Rethink Robotics Research SDK 0.5.2 Release Notes
=================================================

Date: 3/26/2013

Overview
========

The Research SDK provides a platform for roboticists to develop custom 
applications to run on the Baxter hardware platform.

It is designed for high level AI researchers, and those who work at the controls 
level, interested in kinematics, dynamics, force-based algorithms, and 
controlling redundant systems.

See our wiki for more information:

https://github.com/RethinkRobotics/sdk-docs/wiki/Baxter-Overview

System Requirements
===================

https://github.com/RethinkRobotics/sdk-docs/wiki/System-requirements


Installation Instructions
=========================

https://github.com/RethinkRobotics/sdk-docs/wiki/Baxter-Research-Robot-Hardware-Installation-Guide


Additions
=========

*Added ability to control gripper with joystick
*Refactoring of joint_position example
*Added example image for xdisplay example

Removals
========


Changes
=======

*Moved xdisplay to head_control directory
*Changed startup graphic

Fixes
=====
-Collision avoidance regression in urdf
-Velocity commands time out
-Joint drift on joint_position

Issues
======
                                          
-Calibration and Tare scripts will not run if there is a joint error at the head. 
Joint errors can be found in the robot monitor. 
https://github.com/RethinkRobotics/sdk-docs/wiki/Tools---robot_monitor

-When exiting joystick examples, hitting any key will exit example but not the 
joy_node which requires Ctrl-C to exit.

-Wobbler periodically exits with 'failed to disable robot'

